"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-30-Stunning-performances-on-third-day-of-Paris-Olympics-1vEjfMY1mUw-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  Day three of the Paris Olympics gave no shortage of stunning performances, crushing misses, and some surprising delays, as the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s best athletes competed for the coveted medals on the world stage.  China's Lian Junjie and Yang Hao compete in the men's synchronized 10m platform diving final at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on July 29, 2024. PHOTO: SEBASTIEN BOZON / AFP  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Lian Junjie and Yang Hao were awarded Olympic gold medals after winning the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s synchronized 10m platform diving at the Paris Olympics on Monday, July 29, 2024.  Silver medallist China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Xu Jiayu poses with his medal after the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100m backstroke swimming event during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games  PHOTO: JONATHAN NACKSTRAND / AFP  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Xu Jiayu won silver in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100M backstroke final, while players from Team China took the silver medal in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s team gymnastics final on Monday. Japan won the gold while the U.S. claimed the bronze, ending the squad\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 16-year Olympic medal drought.  Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Mollie O\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Callaghan claimed the gold in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 200-meter freestyle. Canadian teenager Summer McIntosh claimed her first gold medal in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 400-meter individual medley.  South Africa received its first gold of the Paris Olympics on Monday as Tatjana Smith won the woman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100-meter breaststroke title, with China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s world champion Tang Qianting winning the silver medal, and Ireland\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Mona McSharry taking the bronze.  Cheung Ka Long from Hong Kong, China, celebrates after winning against Italy\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Filippo Macchi in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s foil individual gold medal bout during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games. PHOTO: FABRICE COFFRINI / AFP  Defending champion Cheung Ka-long of Hong Kong, China, retained his title in men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s foil, beating first-time Olympian Filippo Macchi of Italy 15-14 in a disputed bout.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Yang Junxuan placed fifth in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 200-meter freestyle final.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Wang Xueer and Wan Letian failed to advance to the medal event with a semifinal time of 59.89\\u00a0 and 100.06 respectively in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100-meter backstroke semifinals.  Ukraine claimed its first medal of the Games on Monday in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sabre competition, as Olga Kharlan won bronze for the country, rallying from a six-point deficit to beat Choi Sebin of South Korea.  Manon Apithy-Brunet made history as the first French fencer to win an Olympic title in women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s saber, taking the silver on Monday.  Japan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Yuto Horigome competes in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s street skateboarding final during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games in Paris on July 29, 2024. PHOTO: ODD ANDERSEN / AFP  Japan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Yuto Horigome retained his Olympic men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s street skateboarding title, landing the highest-scoring trick in the final round of Monday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s competition.\\u00a0American Jagger Eaton took the silver, with another U.S. skateboarder Nyjah Huston claiming the bronze.  Christa Deguchi won the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s under 57kg gold medal on Monday, the first-ever Olympic judo title for Canada.  Hidayat Heydarov of Azerbaijan took home gold in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s under 73kg final at the Paris Games.  China advanced with a 3-2 victory in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s volleyball preliminary round, over its first opponent the U.S. on Monday.\\u00a0 The team will now gear up to play the host nation France.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Wang Chuqin (L) and China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Sun Yingsha (R) play a return to South Korea\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Lim Jonghoon and South Korea\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Shin Yubin during their mixed table tennis doubles semifinals at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on July 29, 2024. PHOTO: JUNG YEON-JE / AFP  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Wang Chuqin and Sun Yingsha secured a 4-2 victory over Lim Jong-hoon and Shin Yu-bin of South Korea in the table tennis mixed doubles semifinals on Monday. They will advance to play Ri Jong-sik and Kim Kum-yong of DPRK in the finals.  Olympics surfing was called off in Tahiti after the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s third round on Monday, as the arrival of a storm put an end to the competition for the day.  Organizers of the Games also canceled swimming training in the River Seine on Monday, as they waited to learn if pollution levels will fall low enough to hold the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s triathlon in the river on Tuesday.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"